# Review Rules — Code Review & PR

Version: 4.0.0 | Updated: 2026-05-13 | Applies to: all agents

## 1. Review types & SLAs

| Review type | Applies to | Reviewers | SLA |
|------------|------------|-------------|-----|
| Step review | After each step | PM + Tech Lead (+ step-specific) | 24–48h |
| Code review (PR) | Each PR | Tech Lead (mandatory) + 1 peer | 24h |
| Design review | Steps 3, 5 | UI/UX + Frontend | 24h |
| Security review | Steps 2, 4, 8 | Tech Lead + DevOps | 48h |
| UAT | Step 9 | PM + stakeholders | 3–5d |

**Artifacts:** Per-step criteria → `templates/review-checklists-per-step.md`. Approval format → `templates/approval-request-template.md`. Review quick ref → `.cursor/skills/core/code-review/SKILL.md`. Deep checklists and examples → topic files under `.cursor/skills/core/code-review/references/` (see hub table in `SKILL.md`; manifest `lazy` — load only what you need).

## 2. Tech Lead review — must pass

- Architecture matches agreed design; SOLID; no circular dependencies
- Security: input validation, auth/authz, no injection or sensitive data exposure
- Quality: single responsibility, DRY, clear naming, explicit errors, no PII in logs
- Performance: no N+1; sensible caching; no blocking hot paths
- Tests: business logic covered; coverage meets `core-rules.mdc` gates; edge cases for critical paths
- Docs: public APIs documented; complex logic commented; README/ADR when behavior changes

## 3. PR size & response SLA

| PR size | SLA |
|---------|-----|
| Small (under 100 lines) | 4h |
| Medium (100–300 lines) | 8h |
| Large (300–500 lines) | 24h |
| Very large (over 500 lines) | Split before review |

## 4. Review comment prefixes

| Prefix | Meaning | Must fix? |
|--------|---------|-----------|
| `[BLOCKER]` | Merge blocker | Yes |
| `[IMPORTANT]` | Strong suggestion | Discuss |
| `[SUGGESTION]` | Deferrable | No |
| `[QUESTION]` | Needs answer | Answer |
| `[NITPICK]` | Style | Optional |
| `[PRAISE]` | Positive | No |

## 5. PR merge checklist

- [ ] Tech Lead approved
- [ ] CI green (lint, tests, SAST, build)
- [ ] `[BLOCKER]` and `[IMPORTANT]` resolved
- [ ] No conflicts; PR description (What / Why / How / Testing)
- [ ] `gitnexus pr describe --auto` (or equivalent) when using GitNexus

## 6. Re-review after rejection

Review changed sections only; attach “Changes made”; same reviewer preferred; SLA 12h.
